@{
	ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy for ShinyEggs Electronics";
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8" />
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
	<title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
	<style>

		p {
			margin-bottom: 10px;
		}

		strong {
			font-weight: bold;
		}

		a {
			color: #007BFF;
			text-decoration: none;
		}

			a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}

		/* Center the content div */
		.content {
			max-width: 800px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			display: flex;

		}

		.side-panel {
			min-width: 200px;
			padding-right: 10px;
			position: sticky;
			top: 0;
			left: 0;
			height: 100vh;
			overflow-y: auto;
			padding-top: 60px; 
		}

			.side-panel a {
				display: block;
				margin-bottom: 10px;
				padding: 5px;
			}

				.side-panel a:hover {
					background-color: #f1f1f1;
				}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<!-- Side Panel -->
			<div class="col-md-3 d-none d-md-block">
				<div class="side-panel">
					<a href="#introduction">1. Introduction</a>
					<a href="#information">2. Information We Collect</a>
					<a href="#use-info">3. How We Use Your Information</a>
					<a href="#data-security">4. Data Security</a>
					<a href="#data-sharing">5. Data Sharing</a>
					<a href="#cookies">6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</a>
					<a href="#third-party-links">7. Third-Party Links</a>
					<a href="#children-privacy">8. Children's Privacy</a>
					<a href="#changes">9. Changes to the Privacy Policy</a>
					<a href="#contact">10. Contact Us</a>
				</div>
			</div>


			<!-- Main Content -->
			<div class="col-md-9 col-sm-12">
				<p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 1st July 2023</p>

				<p id="introduction"><strong>1. Introduction</strong></p>
				<p>
					Welcome to ShinyEggs Electronics ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our web application and related services.
				</p>

				<p id="information"><strong>2. Information We Collect</strong></p>
				<p>
					a. Personal Information: We may collect certain personally identifiable information ("Personal Information") from you when you use our web application. This includes but is not limited to your name, email address, shipping address, billing address, phone number, and payment information.
				</p>
				<p>
					b. Non-Personal Information: Additionally, we may collect non-personal information, such as your IP address, browser type, device type, and other technical data, to enhance your user experience and improve our services.
				</p>

				<p id="user-info"><strong>3. How We Use Your Information</strong></p>
				<p>
					a. Personalization: We use your Personal Information to personalize your experience, process your orders, and improve customer service.
				</p>
				<p>
					b. Communication: We may use your email address or phone number to send you important updates, order information, and promotional materials. You can opt-out of marketing communications at any time.
				</p>
				<p>
					c. Payment Processing: We utilize your payment information to process transactions and prevent fraudulent activities.
				</p>
				<p>
					d. Improvement of Services: Non-personal information helps us analyze web application usage patterns, identify technical issues, and enhance our services.
				</p>

				<p id="data-security"><strong>4. Data Security</strong></p>
				<p>
					a. Security Measures: We employ industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
				</p>
				<p>
					b. User Responsibility: While we take reasonable steps to protect your information, remember that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials.
				</p>

				<p id="data-sharing"><strong>5. Data Sharing</strong></p>
				<p>
					a. Third-Party Service Providers: We may share your Personal Information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in delivering our services, such as shipping carriers and payment processors.
				</p>
				<p>
					b. Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or enforceable governmental requests.
				</p>

				<p id="cookies"><strong>6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</strong></p>
				<p>
					a. Cookies: We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your user experience, track your preferences, and analyze web application traffic.
				</p>
				<p>
					b. Opt-Out: You can manage your cookie preferences through your web browser settings.
				</p>

				<p id="third-party-links"><strong>7. Third-Party Links</strong></p>
				<p>
					Our web application may contain links to external sites not operated by us. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party websites. Please review their respective privacy policies.
				</p>

				<p id="children-privacy"><strong>8. Children's Privacy</strong></p>
				<p>
					Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from minors. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with their information, please contact us, and we will take appropriate steps to remove the data.
				</p>

				<p id="changes"><strong>9. Changes to the Privacy Policy</strong></p>
				<p>
					We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective upon posting the revised policy on our web application. Please check this page regularly to stay updated on any revisions.
				</p>

				<p id="contact"><strong>10. Contact Us</strong></p>
				<p>
					If you have any questions, concerns, or requests related to this Privacy Policy or your personal data, please contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@shinyeggs-electronics.com">contact@shinyeggs-electronics.com</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>
